> Fragrant Lamb Noodle Stir-Fry is spiced with lemongrass and Indonesian spices. It's
> perfect for a balanced lifestyle too.

Boil a full #kettle{}.

Trim the @Carrot{1}, then halve lengthways (no need to peel). Slice widthways into
pieces about 1/2 cm thick.

Halve, peel and thinly slice the @Red Onion{1}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} on high heat. Add the carrot
and stir-fry, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Meanwhile, pour the boiled water into a medium #saucepan{} with @salt{1/2%tsp} and
bring to a boil.

Add the @Egg Noodle Nest{125%grams} and cook until tender, ~{4%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and run under cold water to stop them sticking
together.

Reduce the heat of the frying pan to medium-high and add the @Lamb Mince{200%grams},
@Indonesian Style Spice Mix{1%sachet}, sliced onion and @Sliced Mushrooms{120%grams}.
Cook until browned, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Use a #spoon{} to break it up as it cooks, then drain and discard any excess fat.
Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince. It's cooked
> when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, halve and cut the @Lime{1} into wedges.

Add the @Ginger, Garlic & Lemongrass Puree{15%grams} to the pan and stir-fry for
~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in the @Ketjap Manis{50%grams}, @Soy Sauce{25%milliliters} and @Water{100%
milliliters} for the sauce. Simmer until thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add the cooked noodles to the pan and toss through the sauce.

Remove from the heat and add a good squeeze of lime juice.

Taste, season with salt, pepper and more lime juice if needed. Add a splash of
water if it's a little too thick.

Share your lamb noodles between #bowls{}.

Serve with any remaining lime wedges for squeezing over.

Enjoy!